\section{Project Overview and Challenges}
This CompanyTech implementation represents a landmark digital transformation within the raw materials sector, shifting a high-volume production facility from legacy reactive models to a state of advanced Industry 4.0 maturity. By integrating closed-loop optimization and data-driven decision-making, the project successfully addressed systemic process variability and the limitations of manual intervention.

\subsection{Core Challenges}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \highlight{Material Waste:} Incorrect weighing and dosing practices leading to material waste.
    \item \highlight{Recipe Deviations:} Significant recipe deviations from established standards.
    \item \highlight{Human Error:} Heavy reliance on manual recipe adjustments, inducing human error.
    \item \highlight{Operational Difficulty:} Adapting to fluctuations in raw material and supplier properties.
\end{itemize}

\section{Strategic Objectives}
The project established a strategic roadmap to resolve legacy manufacturing hurdles and achieve a superior level of process stability.
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Recipe Forecasting:} Implementation of advanced forecasting models based on raw material and supplier-specific data to preemptively align production parameters.
    \item \textbf{Quality Consistency:} Achieving target quality and color specifications consistently without requiring additional dosing effort or manual overrides.
    \item \textbf{Predictive Analysis:} Developing the high-level capability to predict quality outcomes and material performance prior to the spraying activity.
\end{itemize}

\section{Solution Implementation}
The transformation was executed through a three-pronged strategy designed to stabilize the manufacturing lifecycle and maximize throughput quality.

\subsection{Recipe Management \& Optimization}
This pillar served as the "intelligence layer" of the factory. By utilizing raw material and supplier-specific data, the system automates dosing protocols to eliminate the need for manual recipe adjustments.

\subsection{Grinding \& Milling Optimization}
This phase focused on stabilizing input consistency. By optimizing the grinding and milling parameters, the solution ensures that the physical properties of the raw material are uniform before reaching the dosing stage.

\subsection{Spray Drying Optimization}
The final pillar focused on the predictive control of the spray drying tower. By adjusting parameters in real-time based on upstream data, the system ensures that the output meets strict quality and color specifications.

