\section{Implementation Roadmap}

\subsection{Phase 1: Foundation (Months 1-3)}
\textbf{Milestone:} 95\% recipe accuracy achieved; \$1.5M annual value run-rate. \\
Installation of precision load cells and NIR moisture analyzers. Integration with existing PLC/SCADA systems and data pipeline development.

\subsection{Phase 2: Milling Optimization (Months 4-6)}
\textbf{Milestone:} 8\% energy reduction; 40\% PSD variability reduction. \\
Optimization of comminution processes using reinforcement learning agents and vibration sensor installation on mill trains.

\subsection{Phase 3: Spray Drying Optimization (Months 7-9)}
\textbf{Milestone:} 14\% energy reduction; 68\% defect reduction. \\
Deployment of AI controller for spray drying tower and achievement of predictive quality capabilities.

\subsection{Phase 4: Integration \& Scale (Months 10-12)}
\textbf{Milestone:} \$7.5M annual value achieved. \\
Full system integration, knowledge transfer, operator certification, and preparation for scaling to additional lines.

\section{Lessons Learned and Best Practices}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Data Quality is Paramount:} Invested 30\% of project effort in data cleansing and validation.
    \item \textbf{Physics-Informed AI:} PINNs required 60\% less training data than traditional neural networks and ensured physical feasibility.
    \item \textbf{Operator Engagement:} Involved operators in model validation and interface design, positioning AI as "augmentation".
\end{enumerate}

